cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.AL, cs.GT 

This paper deals with a fundamental routing problem in computer networks, which falls under the category of computer networks and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also presents a deterministic algorithm for this problem, which involves designing and analyzing data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The algorithm's competitiveness is analyzed using game theory (cs.GT) and approximation algorithms (cs.AL). Overall, these sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
